                  <provenance>Additio 1 tells that ʾabuna
                     qasis Rǝʾǝsa Hāymānot donated the book to the
                     church of ʾArāʿro Qǝddus Mikāʾel (located on the plain, close to ʾArāʿro Takla
                     Hāymānot). However, other name(s) have been erased throughout Ms. and replaced
                     by his name (e.g. <locus target="#10rb">10rb</locus>, 28va, 74ra), and other
                     names: Takla Hāymānot (e.g. <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>, 62rb, 81vb),
                     ʾAmḫa Śǝllāse (e.g. <locus target="#9rb">9rb</locus>, 27va, 71rb), ʿĀmata
                     Mikāʾel (<locus target="#22rb">22rb</locus>), Ṣaggā Śǝllāse (e.g. <locus target="#27va">27va</locus>, 51va, 71rb), 
                     Walatta Giyorgis (<locus target="#43va">43va</locus>, 54va, 81vb), Gabra Krǝstos (<locus target="#44ra">44ra</locus>), Kǝfla ʾIyasus (<locus target="#45ra">45ra</locus>), Kǝbrä ʾIyasus (<locus target="#49vb">49vb</locus>), ʿƎśśetä
                     Māryām (<locus target="#51va">51va</locus>), Walda Kidān (<locus target="#54va">54va</locus>), 
                     Walda Rufāʾel (<locus target="#67ra">67ra</locus>). 
                     The names of the relatives of Rǝʾǝsä Hāymānot have been added to the concluding
                     supplication on <locus target="#81va">81va</locus> (wife Walatta Giyorgis and
                     his children ʾAmḫa Śǝllāse, Ṣaggā Śǝllāse).</provenance>
